                     <interp inst="t18121028-95-person1017" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , October, 2d, 1812. Signed, 
               <persName id="t18121028-95-person1018">
                  Joseph 
                  Willis
               <interp inst="t18121028-95-person1018" type="surname" value="Willis"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18121028-95-person1018" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18121028-95-person1018" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>Q. Now, Mr. Jordan, look at that wheat produced by Mr. Davenport - A. It is the same as was in my granary.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Mr. Jordan and the constable told me, if I would tell them they would clear me. I told them the truth. I am very sorry for 
it.</p>


               <p>
                  <rs id="t18121028-95-verdict547" type="verdictDescription">
